[[Category:Chinese traditional date templates]]<templatedata>
{
	"description": "To get the Gregorian year number in the Chinese calendar",
	"params": {
		"1": {
			"aliases": [
				"d"
			],
			"label": "date",
			"description": "the date in the Gregorian calendar.",
			"type": "date",
			"default": "today"
		}
	}
}
</templatedata>
This template is used to obtain the Gregorian year number that corresponds to the current Lunar calendar year. This is useful for January/February, where the Lunar year number before Lunar New Year is one year before.
}}</noinclude>

